# Comparative / context-driven engineering

Before creating a new route/service/template/style:

- Search for **similar existing functionality** and match patterns:
  - FastAPI DI (`app/dependencies.py`)
  - Repository interfaces + implementations (`app/repositories/*`)
  - Service orchestration (`app/services/*`)
  - Template layout and RTL conventions (`app/templates/*`)
  - CSS tokens + dark mode patterns (`app/static/css/style.css`)
  - Security constraints like CSP (no inline scripts) (`app/middleware/security_headers.py`)
- Prefer reuse/refactor of existing helpers over introducing parallel patterns.

